- Handling millions of rows efficiently  
- Standardizing salary formats (annual vs hourly)  
- Removing inconsistencies and null values  
- Data type optimization  

### ðŸ”¹ Data Modeling
- Relationship management  
- Calculated columns and measures  
- KPI development using DAX  
- Trend calculations  

### ðŸ”¹ Data Visualization & Storytelling
- KPI Cards  
- Monthly trend analysis  
- Scatter plot salary comparison  
- Drill-through functionality  
- Geographic job distribution map  
- Interactive filtering  



## ðŸ“Š Dashboard Structure


### ðŸŸ¦ Page 1: High-Level Market View

![Dashboard Page 1](images/Dashboard.png)

This page provides a macro-level overview of the 2024 data job market.

#### Key Insights:

- **~478K job postings analyzed**
- **$113K average annual salary**
- **$49.37 average hourly salary**
- Data Engineer is the most demanded role
- Engineering-focused roles show higher compensation

#### Visual Components:

- KPI Summary Cards  
- Monthly Job Trend (2024)  
- Salary Comparison (Annual vs Hourly)  
- Job Count by Role  
- Detailed Salary & Trend Table  

This page enables quick market benchmarking and demand comparison.

---

### ðŸŸ¦ Page 2: Job Title Drill-Through Analysis

![Dashboard Page 2](images/DrillThrough.png)

This page allows deep analysis by specific job title using drill-through functionality.

Example shown: **Data Engineer**

#### Detailed Analysis Includes:

- Annual salary gauge (Minâ€“Max range)
- Hourly salary gauge
- Remote work percentage
- Education requirement indicator
- Benefits availability
- Geographic distribution (Global map)
- Top hiring platforms
- Work modality breakdown (Full-time vs Contractor)

This enables role-specific salary benchmarking and market positioning.


## ðŸ“ˆ Key Findings

- Data Engineer leads market demand in 2024.
- Machine Learning Engineer and Senior Data Scientist are among the highest-paid roles.
- Approximately 89% of roles are Full-time.
- Many job postings do not explicitly require a university degree.
- LinkedIn dominates as the primary hiring platform.
- Remote work is present but not dominant.


